Podocarpus elatus

   [8785.jpg]
   Authority R. Br.
   Family Pinopsida:Podocarpaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names weeping podocarpus, she-pine, brown pine, podocarpo de
   ramos pendentes
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 8785

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: A medium sized to tall tree reaching 40 m in height, while
   the trunk may reach 90 cm in diameter. The trunk is often irregular,
   especially at the base. The crown is dense and dark-green. The tree
   does not have cones like other conifers but instead have a single seed
   attached by a fleshy stem to the branch. USE: Wood used for turnery,
   furniture, joinery, musical instruments, boat planking and piles in
   salt water. The fleshy stems of the seeds were eaten by Aboriginal
   people in some parts of Australia. GROWING PERIOD: Fast growing
   perennial, taking 8 to 10 years to reach maturity. COMMON NAMES: Brown
   pine, She pine, Yellow pine, Plum pine. FURTHER INF: In Australia, the
   latitudinal range of the tree is 14-35Â°S and it occur at elevations
   between sea level and 1000 m. It grows in dense subtropical, riverine
   and seashore rainforests. The best development is obtained in coastal
   lowlands on deep alluvial soils besides river banks. It is fire
   resistant.

   Sources
   SOURCES (P. elatus R. Br. ex Endl.)(23.05.02) E8785
   Boland D 1984 pp 62-64 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, TEXT, DEP, DRA, FER, PH USE]

